sky.engine.util
Class SortedArray<T>

java.lang.Object
  sky.engine.util.SortedArray<T>
Type Parameters:
T - - Class type for the objects to be sorted.
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.util.Collection<T>, java.util.List<T>
public class SortedArray<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.List<T>

An implementation of a Sorted Array. It is constructed using a Comparator object that can compare two objects together, thus allowing the SortedArray to order its elements into ascending or descending order. We can also create a SortedArray without a Comparator object, if and only if the objects to be used implement the Comparable interface. This is similar to the SortedList, but far more efficient.

Author:
Matthew Kelly (Badgerati).
